----------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party firmware (NOT redistributed by this project)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

cdj3k-emu emulates Pioneer DJ's CDJ-3000 hardware.  It requires the user to
supply their own copy of a Pioneer CDJ-3000 firmware update file (.UPD) on
first launch.  The in-app wizard decrypts the update locally, extracts the
kernel + rootfs onto a per-user qcow2 disk image under
"~/Library/Application Support/com.cdj3k.emu/", and never transmits it
elsewhere.

