----------------------------------------------------------------------
Bundled and dynamically loaded third-party components
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The build pipeline and the final .app bundle include or invoke the
following projects.  Each retains its upstream license; the names below
identify the SPDX expression that governs the redistributed copy.

  * QEMU                  https://www.qemu.org/                  GPL-2.0-or-later
    Built from upstream source; our patches in qemu/patches/ and the
    embedding shim in qemu/shim/ are GPL-2.0-or-later derivatives.

  * Linux kernel          https://kernel.org/                    GPL-2.0
    Built from upstream 6.6 LTS source (see docker/Dockerfile for the
    pinned tag).  Our patches in guest/kernel-patches/ and the
    out-of-tree modules in guest/modules/ are GPL-2.0-or-later.

  * socket_vmnet          https://github.com/lima-vm/socket_vmnet
                                                                 Apache-2.0
    Fetched at bundle time by bundle.sh (pinned by version + SHA-256).
    Bundled inside Contents/MacOS/ of the distributed .app.

  * BusyBox               https://busybox.net/                   GPL-2.0-only
    Present inside the guest rootfs.  Source available from the upstream
    project; the firmware wizard relies on the BusyBox already present in
    the user-supplied Pioneer firmware and does not bundle a separate copy.

  * dropbear              https://matt.ucc.asn.au/dropbear/      MIT-style
    Present inside the guest rootfs.  Configured by the initramfs patch
    scripts under initramfs-patch/patch-rootfs.d/ when ENABLE_SSH=1 (off
    by default).  No private keys are committed; keys are generated at
    first boot when SSH is enabled.

  * LZ4                   https://github.com/lz4/lz4             BSD-2-Clause
    Linked statically into the guest kernel image (LZ4 ramdisk decompression)
    and used by guest user-space tools for stream framing.  Inherited from
    upstream Linux.

  * glibc, libdrm, ALSA, Xorg, and other Linux user-space components inside
    the guest rootfs retain their upstream licenses (LGPL-2.1+, MIT, MIT,
    MIT respectively, among others).  Sources are obtainable from the
    upstream projects; docker/Dockerfile documents the exact versions.

  * xserver-xorg-video-dummy   Debian/Ubuntu source package      MIT
    Repackaged from the upstream Ubuntu 20.04 (focal) arm64 .deb.  Used to
    provide the Xorg dummy video driver ABI 24.0 inside the guest.

  * Nimbus Sans L,        URW++ Type Foundry                    AGPL-3.0-or-later
    Nimbus Sans T           with font exception (URW Nimbus core)
    https://www.urwtype.com/
    Bundled as .otf in app/cdj3k-emu/assets/.  Distributed under the GPL
    font exception, which permits embedding in documents and applications
    without imposing the GPL on those works.  The .otf files are the
    unmodified URW++ release.

  * Apple Hypervisor.framework, AuthorizationServices, vmnet.framework,
    CoreAudio, AppKit and other macOS APIs are linked dynamically at runtime
    and governed by Apple's macOS SDK License.

